   <titles>
      <title>Linear Combination and Span</title>
      <plain.title>Span</plain.title>
   </titles>
   <intro>
      <block>
         <block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>The span operation applied to a set of vectors <math>
                     <latex>S</latex>
                  </math> in <math>
                     <latex>\RNr[n]</latex>
                  </math> yields a subvector space of <math>
                     <latex>\RNr[n]</latex>
                  </math> through the following process:</para.body>
            </para>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>A linear combination of vectors <math>
                           <latex>\Vect{s}_1,\dots ,\Vect{s}_r</latex>
                        </math> in <math>
                           <latex>S</latex>
                        </math> is a vector <math>
                           <latex>\Vect{x}</latex>
                        </math> in <math>
                           <latex>\RNr[n]</latex>
                        </math> of the form</para.body>
                  </para>
                  <math.array column="3">
                     <row rowspan="1">
                        <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                           <math>
                              <latex>\Vect{x}</latex>
                           </math>
                        </cell>
                        <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                           <math>
                              <latex>=</latex>
                           </math>
                        </cell>
                        <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                           <math>
                              <latex>t_1 \Vect{s}_1 + \cdots + t_r \Vect{s}_r</latex>
                           </math>
                        </cell>
                     </row>
                  </math.array>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>where <math>
                           <latex>t_1,\dots ,t_r</latex>
                        </math> are numbers in <math>
                           <latex>\RNr</latex>
                        </math>.</para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>The span of <math>
                           <latex>S</latex>
                        </math> is the set of all possible linear combinations of vectors in <math>
                           <latex>S</latex>
                        </math>.</para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
            </ol>
            <para>
               <para.body>Details follow:</para.body>
            </para>
         </block.body>
      </block>
   </intro>
